							<hr width="100%" size="1" class="hrcolor" />
							<div class="post">A single logic-level N-Channel MOSFET should work, assuming you don&#039;t need to run in reverse.&nbsp; Connect &quot;Source&quot; pin to 24V Minus and Arduino Ground.&nbsp; Connect &quot;Drain&quot; pin to the motor&#039;s Minus side.&nbsp; Connect the &quot;Gate&quot; pin through a 1k resistor to an Arduino PWM pin.&nbsp; Connect the Plus side of the motor to the 24V Plus.<br /><br />ON Semiconductor 2SK4043LS has a logic-level gate and can handle 20A and 30V.&nbsp; </div>
